RapidEnv Example Java EE
========================

This is an example of a Jave EE development environment
with JBoss, Maven and Eclipse that demonstrates the power
of automated installation, configuration and update by RapidEnv.


Highlights:
-----------

* based on one single configuration file (environment/env.xml, size < 50 kB)
  the small but powerful Java tool RapidEnv (size < 5 MB) helps you to install
  and set up a complex development einvironment (size around 1000 MB) without
  any or with only a few user interactions.

* development environment specific operating system environment variables
  are controlled completely locally without polluting the global environment.

* Desktop and start menu icons are provided to start and stop or launch
  the components of the development environment.


Software installed:
-------------------

The RapidEnv environement setup and maintenance tool will set up
a standard development environment consisting in the following
software:
- jdk      Java SE Development Kit (including Java Runtime Environment)
           version 1.6.0_26 (upgrade to 1.7.0_2)
- maven    Maven build system
           version 3.0.3
- jboss    JBoss Application Server
           version 6.0.0.Final, (upgrade to 7.0.2.Final)
- eclipse  Eclipse IDE for Java EE developers SR2
           version 3.6.2 / Helios SR2, 3.7.1 (upgrade to 3.7.1 / Indigo SR1)
  - plugin jbosstools   JBoss integration into Eclipse
                        Version 3.2.0.GA.aggregate-Update-2011-02-16_18-30-44-H329

System Requirements:
--------------------

2 GB of Space on your harddiskhttps://github.com/downloads/bluemel/RapidEnvExampleJavaEE/RapidEnvExampleJavaEE-0.9.1.zip

RapidEnv currently basically works under Windows and Linux.
It has been tested so far with:
- Windows XP
- OpenSUSE Linux 11.4

A Java Runtime Environment (Version 1.6.x) has to be
installed in order to run the RapidEnv command line tool "renv".


Download and install the example:
---------------------------------

The GIT way:

  If you have installed the GIT version controly system you

- Open a Windows command prompt or Unix terminal window and
  go to the folder where you want the example to be installed

- type command
  git clone git@github.com:bluemel/RapidEnv.git

Without version control:

   Simply download and unpack example archive
   https://github.com/downloads/bluemel/RapidEnvExampleJavaEE/RapidEnvExampleJavaEE-0.9.1.zip


Use Cases:
----------

  1) Use Case: Setup
     Initial development environment setup
     ----------------------------------------

  - Open a Windows command prompt or Unix terminal window
    in folder RapidEnvExampleJavaEE/environment/bin

  - start RapidEnv by entering command:
    - Windows> renv -yes
    - Linux>   . renv -yes
      Prepending . on Linux is essential to influence the
      environment settings of the current shell window.

    This will install the development environment without
    any user interaction in 15 - 30 minutes depending of the
    speed of your internet connection and harddisk.

    On Linux typing the root user's password once might be
    necessary after 1 to 2 minutes because the JDK installation
    requires root user rights.

  Celebrate:
    * Development environment specific command prompt
    * Output of renv command
    * Environment set
    * Start and stop command for jboss
    * Desktop and start menu icons
    * Eclipse with configured JBoss integration (JBoss Tools plugin)


  2) Use Case: Upgrade 
     Version upgrade of different parts of the development envrionment
     -----------------------------------------------------------------

   !!! Please Note: this Use Case is currently under construction and
       may not work yet completely !!!

   - edit environment configuration file
     RapidEnvExampleJavaEE/environment/env.xml

     - configure upgrade of install unit "jdk"
       from version 1.6.0_26 to version 1.7.0_2
       by the following changes:

       - version
         --> "1.7.0_2"

       - value of property "uversion"
         --> "7u2"
       - value of property "buildnumber"
         ---> "b13"

       - MD5 hashvalues of the source file checks:
         windows:
         ---> "7b0bb440d5659faeadda44b3ebd63841"
         linux:
         ---> "?????? <to be detemined> ???????"

     - configure upgrade of install unit "jboss"
       from version 6.0.0.Final to version 7.0.2.Final
       by the following changes:

       - version
         --> "7.0.2.Final"

       - sourcefile
         --> jboss-as-web-''version().zip

       - sourceurl
         --> http://download.jboss.org/jbossas/7.0/jboss-as-''version()/jboss-as-web-''version().zip

       - MD5 hashvalue of the source file check:
         ---> "eb2d9f58d030fcb4d9a255a9ba6052c2"

       - configure JBoss 7 start commands on Windows / Linux
         by commenting in / out the associated XML blocks
         !!! please note replace the "XX" by "--" (a tribute to working with XML comments)
         <insert line="homedir()\bin\jboss-admin.bat XXconnect command=:shutdown"
         --->
         <insert line="homedir()\bin\jboss-admin.bat --connect command=:shutdown" 

     - configure upgrade of install unit "eclipse"
       from version 3.2.6 to version 3.7.1
       by the following changes:

       - version
         --> "3.7.1"

       - MD5 hashvalues of the source file checks:
         windows:
         ---> "48647f4b3b2bb559fbcd8a428dc7a638"
         linux:
         ---> "xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"

       - property "distname"
         ---> value="indigo"

       - property name="servicerelease"
         ---> value="SR1"

     - configure upgrade of sub install unit "eclipse/jbosstools"
       from version 3.2.0.GA.aggregate-Update-2011-02-16_18-30-44-H329
       to version 3.3.0.M5.aggregate-Update-2011-12-14_19-42-13-H61
       by the following changes:

       - version
         --> "3.3.0.M5.aggregate-Update-2011-12-14_19-42-13-H61"

       - sourceurl
         --> "http://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/jboss/JBossTools/JBossTools3.3.0.x/jbosstools-3.3.0.M5.aggregate-Update-2011-12-14_19-42-13-H61.zip?r=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.jboss.org%2Ftools%2Fdownload%2Fdev.html&amp;ts=1326784317&amp;use_mirror=dfn"

       - MD5 hashvalue of the source file check:
         ---> "ce6de1b9accc8b2c31ed000705e247c6"

       - XML file ${eclipse.workspace}/.metadata/.plugins/org.eclipse.ui.workbench/workbench.xml

         - setnodevale
           ---> path = "//workbench/mruList/file[@id='org.eclipse.wst.server.ui.editor' and @name='JBoss 7.0 Runtime Server']/@factoryID"

         - setnodevalue:
           ---> path = "//workbench/mruList/file[@id='org.eclipse.wst.server.ui.editor' and @name='JBoss 7.0 Runtime Server']/@tooltip"
           ---> value = "JBoss 7.0 Runtime Server"

         - setnodevalue:
           ---> path = "//workbench/mruList/file[@id='org.eclipse.wst.server.ui.editor' and @name='JBoss 7.0 Runtime Server']/@tooltip"
           ---> value = "JBoss 7.0 Runtime Server1320073606750"

         - setnodevalue
           ---> path = "//workbench/mruList/file[@id='org.eclipse.wst.server.ui.editor' and @name='JBoss 7.0 Runtime Server']/persistable/@server-id"
           ---> value = "JBoss 7.0 Runtime Server1320073606750"

       - Properties file ${eclipse.workspace}/.metadata/.plugins/org.eclipse.core.runtime/.settings/org.jboss.ide.eclipse.as.ui.prefs"

         - setpropvalue name="org.jboss.ide.eclipse.as.ui.defaultWebServer"
           ---> value="JBoss 7.0 Runtime Server1320073606750"

         - setpropvalue name="org.jboss.ide.eclipse.as.ui.wizards.LAST_SERVER_CREATED"
           ---> value="JBoss 7.0 Runtime Server1320073606750"

         - setpropvalue (replace rg.jboss.ide.eclipse.as.ui.preferences.runtime.last.type.org.jboss.ide.eclipse.as.runtime.60)
           ---> name="org.jboss.ide.eclipse.as.ui.preferences.runtime.last.type.org.jboss.ide.eclipse.as.runtime.70"

   - Open development environment specific Windows command prompt
    or Unix terminal window using
    - Windows Explorex context menu entry
    - or KDE Dolphin "Actions" menu entry
    - or Gnome Nautilus "Scripts" menu entry
      "RapidEnvJavaEE Command Prompt main"

  - start RapidEnv by entering command:
    - Windows> renv update
    - Linux>   . renv update

  Celebrate:
    * Environment changed
    * New versions installed and runnable


  3) Teardown
     Removal of the complete development environment
     -----------------------------------------------

  - Open development environment specific Windows command prompt
    or Unix terminal window using
    - Windows Explorer context menu entry
      "RapidEnvJavaEE Command Prompt main"
    - Linux KDE Dolphin "Actions" menu entry
      "Open Terminal RapidEnvJavaEE main"
    - Linux Gnome Nautilus "Scripts" menu entry
      "Open Terminal RapidEnvJavaEE main"

  - start RapidEnv by entering command:
    - Windows> renv deinstall
    - Linux>   . renv deinstall

  - remove folder RapidEnvExampleJavaEE from the
    file system.

  Celebrate:
    * your development environment has completely been
      wiped out without any trace left including
      file manager, desktop and start menu entries.


